Job Description:
As a Data Scientist, you will join the Data Science Enterprise Risk Management (“ERM”) team that is responsible for data governance/management and introducing data automation initiatives that increases overall efficiencies and efficacy that drives faster data and risk-based decision-making across the Bank. This role is expected to direct, plan, and oversee delivery of deeper data analysis to others at the Bank. Additionally, this position is intended to leverage data-driven insights and advanced data modeling techniques to support the mission of the bank and bolster the identification, assessment, monitoring, management, and reporting of risks.
Success in this role entails knowledge of general data analytics techniques, along with broad expertise in risk management areas including, but not limited to, operational risk, credit/collateral risk, and market risk. This role is at the intersection of leadership, business support, and engagement that will span across teams and business units. The role will be an integral part of an expanding Data Science team that encourages creativity, leadership, and influence. You are expected to have a significant impact and influence in bank-wide strategic decision making to support our mission through data-powered products, streamlined processes, analytics services, and business policies.
Key Accountabilities:
Play a lead role in developing a high-performance data platform, integrating data from a variety of internal and external sources, in order to support data and analytics activities across the Bank;
Design and develop scalable data processing infrastructure, utilizing innovative frameworks to drive efficiency and promote automation;
Assist the ERM team with strategy-implementation and improvement opportunities;
Write and present clear and concise reports/presentations containing meaningful observations and recommendations/conclusions, and document procedures performed;
Build business intelligence and create visualization to present analysis findings to business stakeholders;
Lead outreach efforts to showcase and share core capabilities, leading data analytics practices, key insights, and modernization opportunities;
Develop key performance indicators (“KPIs”) and Key Risk Indicators (“KRIs”) and dashboards to support optimization of internal processes;
Resolve problems through in-depth evaluation of business processes, system processes, enterprise policies and procedures;
Solve critical business objectives in a variety of business areas that can include credit risk, market risk, and operational risk categories;
Identify and drive areas for quick wins in the near term, while keeping an eye on how those wins fit into an overall long-term data infrastructure and analytics activities strategy;
Assist in preparing monthly enterprise risk reporting and in the presentation of materials to the ERC; and
Take ownership of data science projects and deliver high-quality results.
Critical Competencies:
3+ years of data engineering experience and in financial analytics;
Experience in data architecture, data manipulation, cleansing, and transformation leading to a cohesive data strategy;
Experience with Exchange, Transform, and Load (“ETL”) design concepts and development;
Experience in developing cloud ETL and date pipeline with various technologies such as Python, AWS Sagemaker, Airflow, Talend, AWS Lambda, MongoDB, Jenkins, and AWS Dynamo;
Hands-on data processing and database data modeling experience and strong level understanding of ETL fundamentals and building and maintaining efficient data pipelines;
Demonstrated ability to identify business and technical impacts of user requirements and incorporate them into the project schedule;
Expert Knowledge of SQL, R / Python, VBA Macros and ability to write code independently;
Experience with modern software delivery practices, including source control, testing, production implementation, and continuous delivery using API, Python, SQL and AWS services;
Excellent organization and project management skills and able to work independently;
Ability to organize, prioritize, and complete multiple tasks in a high paced environment;
Must have excellent interpersonal skills to work in a team environment and to influence and interface with a broad range of stakeholders at all levels, both internal and external; and
Able to communicate complex analytical insights in a simple, concise manner, and to build strong relationships with various business units to effectively convert insights into action.
